    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-31T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="1356"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1356">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/8–3149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jones</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">at Nanking</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-31T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 31, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1038. ReDeptels 1028 to Nanking and 1727 to Shanghai Aug 26.<note n="49"
                        xml:id="d1356fn49">Neither printed.</note> It is Dept’s intention and hope
                    Emb and ConGen can arrange for all departing personnel use first available
                    transportation. Every effort shld be made get personnel departing aboard <hi
                        rend="italic">Gordon</hi>. If Dept has not issued trans orders for personnel
                    transferring, Nanking shld issue evacuation TO’s and inform Dept nr, date, names
                    of employees and families and destination evacuation TO’s.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking rptd Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
